Inter Milan have officially confirmed the signing of defender, Ashley Young from Manchester United. Young, who spent over eight years with Man United, will now wear the number-fifteen shirt at Inter. The club disclosed this in a statement posted on its official website on Friday. The statement read: “MILAN – After officially joining Inter from Manchester United, Ashley Young has chosen the shirt number he will wear during his Nerazzurri adventure: the number 15! “It will soon be possible to purchase the shirt of the English wideman at store.inter.it, the Inter Store Milano and the San Siro Store.” Young, 34, will now hope to feature for Antonio Conte’s side when they take on Lecce in an away Serie A fixture on Sunday.